    "opportunities for students' to become aware of biases through firsthand experiences with LLMs trained on data they have categorized themselves, for teachers to build competences while working with researchers, and challenges in the form of designing appropriate tools for students and teachers to recognize the potential of learning about, and create with, AI.",
    "Hence, research such as this will provide guidance of how best to prepare and educate a new generation of students and teachers to understand, interact with, and create generative AI systems that are suited to their specific needs in life.",
    "Re-situating the salience of context in designing for authentic engagement with AI/ML-based design for athletics and play Herminio Bodon, Meg Butler, Khushbu Kshirsagar, Vishesh Kumar, Michael Smith, Ashley Quiterio, Marcelo Worsley As learning scientists, we often remind people that learning takes place across a wide variety of contexts.",
    "In this presentation we will focus on what it looks like to design for learning AI/ML across a number of different sportsrelated contexts.",
    "Sports represent a unique social phenomena."
